WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:03.298
The FX original series,
The Americans.

00:03.330 --> 00:05.662
The new season,
Wednesdays at 10:00 on FX.

00:08.070 --> 00:09.469
PREVIOUSLY ON
"THE AMERICANS"...

00:09.510 --> 00:11.137
Stan: I THINK YOUR DEFECTOR
MIGHT BE A RUSSIAN SPY.

00:11.170 --> 00:12.637
IF I CAN PROVE IT,
WE'LL ARREST HER.

00:12.680 --> 00:15.672
THEN THERE'S A GOOD CHANCE
MY GOVERNMENT CAN MAKE A TRADE.

00:15.710 --> 00:16.870
FOR NINA.

00:16.910 --> 00:19.470
PAIGE WILL HAVE A CHOICE.

00:19.520 --> 00:21.841
SHE'S NOT EQUIPPED
TO DEAL WITH THIS SHIT!
[ CUP SLAMS ]

00:21.880 --> 00:23.347
PHILIP.

00:24.520 --> 00:26.181
Hanson: [Voice breaking ]
THEY FOUND THE PEN.

00:26.220 --> 00:29.348
I MET A MAN NAMED
WALTER TAFFET YESTERDAY.

00:29.390 --> 00:30.527
WHO'S HE?

00:30.560 --> 00:32.357
WELL, HE'S YOU.

00:33.100 --> 00:34.692
WHO ARE YOU?

00:51.580 --> 00:52.717
HI.

00:52.750 --> 00:54.047
HEY.

00:54.080 --> 00:56.241
WE DID GOOD,
DIDN'T WE?

01:00.390 --> 01:04.850
I THINK TODD MAY HAVE SEEN YOU
AS WE LEFI' THE FACTORY.

01:04.890 --> 01:07.199
TH-THAT. ..

01:07.230 --> 01:08.527
IS NOT POSSIBLE.

01:08.560 --> 01:10.926
I CAUGHT A GLIMPSE OF YOU
AT THE BOTTOM OF THE LADDER

01:10.970 --> 01:13.029
WHEN WE WERE LEAVING.

01:13.070 --> 01:14.367
CAME DOWN TOO SOON.

01:14.400 --> 01:17.858
YOU TH-- YOU THINK
HE MAY HAVE SEEN ME?

01:17.910 --> 01:20.538
YEAH.
YOU DON'T KNOW FOR SURE.

01:20.580 --> 01:21.706
I DON'T HAVE TO.

01:21.740 --> 01:24.402
HANS, IT'S OVER.

01:24.450 --> 01:26.145
US. THIS.

01:27.750 --> 01:30.548
YOU'VE TRAINED ME WELL.
WE'VE -- WE'VE WORKED SO HARD.

01:30.590 --> 01:32.046
I CAN'T TAKE THAT RISK.

01:32.090 --> 01:34.217
I WANT TO SERVE.

01:34.260 --> 01:36.581
I WA-- I WANT TO BE OF USE
TO OUR CAUSE.

01:36.630 --> 01:38.052
YOU WILL.

01:38.090 --> 01:39.751
YOU'LL JUST SERVE
IN OTHER WAYS.

01:51.310 --> 01:53.778
[ COPY MACHINE WHIRRING ]

01:53.810 --> 01:56.677
[ TELEPHONE RINGING ]

01:57.680 --> 02:00.114
MORNING.
MORNING.

02:07.290 --> 02:10.350
THE FBI FOUND THE BUG
IN GAAD'S PEN.

02:17.970 --> 02:19.631
DOES GABRIEL KNOW?

02:21.670 --> 02:23.638
NOT YET. [ SIGHS ]

02:27.810 --> 02:30.108
THERE IS MORE.

02:30.150 --> 02:31.970
MARTHA KNOWS ABOUT ME.

02:32.010 --> 02:34.444
HOW?

02:34.480 --> 02:38.985
THE PERSON THEY BROUGHT IN
TO INVESTIGATE ISN'T ME.

02:39.020 --> 02:41.614
DOES SHE KNOW
THAT YOU'RE --

02:41.660 --> 02:43.480
NO.
YOU'RE SURE?

02:45.230 --> 02:47.494
SHE DOESN'T WANT TO KNOW
MORE THAN SHE HAS TO.

02:50.230 --> 02:51.322
WHAT DO WE DO?

02:51.370 --> 02:54.635
[ INHALES,
EXHALES DEEPLY ]

02:54.670 --> 02:56.706
NOTHING.

02:58.540 --> 03:00.132
DOING NOTHING
IS A BAD IDEA.

03:00.180 --> 03:02.034
WE NEED
TO GIVE IT TIME.

03:02.080 --> 03:03.638
[ SIGHS ]

03:03.680 --> 03:05.705
HOW MUCH TIME
ARE WE TALKING ABOUT, PHILIP?

03:05.750 --> 03:08.639
I'LL LET YOU KNOW.
I'M GOING BACK THERE TONIGHT.

03:08.680 --> 03:11.217
WHAT? WHY?

03:11.250 --> 03:13.980
PHILIP, YOU CAN'T.

03:14.020 --> 03:15.385
IF SHE'S TOLD ANYONE --

03:15.420 --> 03:16.648
SHE HASN'T TOLD ANYONE.

03:16.690 --> 03:20.353
HOW DO YOU KNOW?
HOW CAN YOU KNOW?

03:22.270 --> 03:24.522
BECAUSE I TRUST HER.

03:38.610 --> 03:42.580
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER
IN DISTANCE ]

03:47.890 --> 03:49.289
[ CAR DOOR CLOSES ]

03:51.390 --> 03:53.051
[ LIQUID BUBBLING ]

03:53.100 --> 03:54.556
MMM.

03:56.730 --> 03:59.221
[ LIQUID POURS ]

04:04.740 --> 04:07.402
HI.

04:07.440 --> 04:08.702
HI.

04:08.740 --> 04:10.549
I WENT TO THE MARKET

04:10.580 --> 04:13.048
AND GOT FRESH BASIL
AND PLUM TOMATOES.

04:13.080 --> 04:14.718
I THOUGHT ABOUT
LINGUINI WITH CLAMS,

04:14.750 --> 04:16.741
BUT THE TOMATOES
LOOKED TOO GOOD.

04:18.120 --> 04:21.578
COME HERE.
HAVE A TASTE.

04:26.930 --> 04:29.797
[ SLURPS ]

04:29.830 --> 04:30.967
IT'S DELICIOUS.

04:31.000 --> 04:33.139
IT'S NOT TOO SPICY?
PERFECT.

04:33.170 --> 04:34.899
[ TELEPHONE RINGING ]

04:34.940 --> 04:38.239
MM. CAN YOU STIR?

04:38.270 --> 04:41.433
YOU KNOW HOW TO STIR,
DON'T YOU?

04:46.110 --> 04:47.816
HELLO?

04:47.850 --> 04:50.944
THIS IS SHE.

04:50.990 --> 04:53.788
IT'S CHILDREN'S SERVICES.

04:53.820 --> 04:56.459
I-I'M SORRY.
I HAVEN'T BEEN HOME ALL DAY.

04:56.490 --> 04:59.129
WELL,
THE CHILDREN ARE WONDERFUL.

04:59.160 --> 05:02.425
UM...BUT
WE'VE RECONSIDERED.

05:02.470 --> 05:07.260
IT'S JUST NOT A GOOD TIME.
IT'S NOT THE RIGHT TIME.

05:07.300 --> 05:09.268
MM-HMM. YES.

05:09.300 --> 05:11.006
OF COURSE.
IF THINGS CHANGE...

05:11.040 --> 05:13.770
THANK YOU SO MUCH.

05:13.810 --> 05:15.107
THANK YOU.

05:15.140 --> 05:17.108
[ RECEIVER HANGS UP ]

05:17.150 --> 05:19.948
IT'S UNREALISTIC
TO THINK ABOUT CHILDREN.

05:19.980 --> 05:21.948
NOT NOW.

05:21.980 --> 05:23.641
IT'S UNREALISTIC.

05:26.820 --> 05:28.959
CLARK?
[ SIGHS ]

05:28.990 --> 05:30.787
IT'S OKAY.

05:30.830 --> 05:32.457
REALLY.

05:32.500 --> 05:35.298
IT'S FINE. I'M FINE.

05:35.330 --> 05:38.891
I JUST NEEDED TO KNOW.

05:41.340 --> 05:42.659
AND NOW I DO.

05:45.710 --> 05:47.507
OKAY?

05:47.540 --> 05:50.805
YEAH.

05:50.850 --> 05:53.410
WHY DON'T YOU SIT?

06:18.110 --> 06:21.034
THANK YOU.

06:28.420 --> 06:30.547
TO TURNING THE PAGE.

06:37.890 --> 06:41.394
MMM.

06:41.430 --> 06:44.092
[ SIGHS ]

06:44.130 --> 06:46.735
SO...

06:51.770 --> 06:55.206
...AGENT GAAD IS UNDER
SO MUCH PRESSURE

06:55.240 --> 06:57.447
WITH THIS INVESTIGATION.

06:57.480 --> 07:00.711
I'M NOT SURE
HE'S GONNA MAKE IT.

07:00.750 --> 07:02.889
HE LOST HIS COOL
YESTERDAY

07:02.920 --> 07:05.582
IN A WAY
THAT HE NEVER HAS BEFORE.

07:05.620 --> 07:09.408
HE ACTUALLY ATI'ACKED
THE MAIL ROBOT.

07:09.460 --> 07:11.724
AND GENE
COULDN'T FIX IT.

07:11.760 --> 07:15.821
THEY'RE SENDING IT OUT
FOR REPAIRS.

07:19.270 --> 07:22.398
[ SIGHS ]

07:22.440 --> 07:24.408
WHO'S GENE?

07:24.440 --> 07:28.399
HE'S OUR
COMPUTER SPECIALIST.

07:28.440 --> 07:31.477
HE'S IN CHARGE OF
THE MAIL ROBOT.

07:31.510 --> 07:33.910
IT WAS ACTUALLY HIS IDEA

07:33.950 --> 07:37.147
TO UPGRADE
THE MESSAGE-DELIVERY SYSTEM.

07:41.190 --> 07:46.696
OKAY, MANGIA, SWEETIE,
BEFORE IT GETS COLD.

08:32.010 --> 08:35.173
[ WATER DRIPPING ]

08:46.520 --> 08:48.351
[ SNIFFLES ]

08:48.390 --> 08:49.857
YOU MAY BE RIGHT...

08:51.030 --> 08:53.328
...ABOUT ZINAIDA.

08:53.360 --> 08:56.818
WHAT DID YOU FIND OUT?

08:56.870 --> 09:01.034
NOTHING DEFINITE,
BUT, UH...

09:01.070 --> 09:03.209
I WAS LOOKING AROUND
THE REZIDENTURA,

09:03.240 --> 09:04.537
ASKING QUESTIONS.

09:04.570 --> 09:08.870
AND, UH...
SOMETHING DOESN'T SEEM RIGHT.

09:10.880 --> 09:14.338
I HAVE A WAY
WE CAN KNOW FOR SURE.

09:14.380 --> 09:15.517
IT'S RISKY.

09:15.550 --> 09:17.211
[ SNIFFLES ]

09:17.250 --> 09:19.184
BUT IT'S NINA'S
ONLY HOPE.

09:19.220 --> 09:21.415
HOW RISKY?

09:21.460 --> 09:23.257
IF WE GET CAUGHT...

09:23.290 --> 09:25.850
[ SNIFFLES ]

09:25.890 --> 09:27.096
...VERY.

09:50.620 --> 09:52.247
[ CLA'ITER ]

09:52.660 --> 09:55.379
[ SHOUTING ]

09:55.420 --> 09:57.388
[ GUN CLICKS ]

09:57.430 --> 09:58.988
[ GRUNTING ]

10:06.430 --> 10:09.763
[ GRUNTING CONTINUES ]

10:33.160 --> 10:35.697
[ GASPING ]

10:56.650 --> 10:58.447
[ GRUNTS ]

10:58.490 --> 11:01.857
[ BREATHES HEAVILY ]

11:01.890 --> 11:04.188
Gabriel:
THE FBI WON'T STOP

11:04.230 --> 11:06.619
TILL THEY FIND
WHO PUT THE BUG IN GAAD'S PEN.

11:06.660 --> 11:08.525
THEY HAVE
A BUILDING FULL OF SUSPECTS.

11:08.560 --> 11:10.619
DO YOU THINK MARTHA
CAN KEEP IT TOGETHER

11:10.670 --> 11:12.194
DURING
A LONG INVESTIGATION?

11:12.230 --> 11:14.790
YEAH, I THINK SO.

11:14.840 --> 11:17.536
WE'VE NEVER SEEN HER
UNDER THAT KIND OF PRESSURE.

11:17.570 --> 11:18.662
SHE'LL PROTECT ME.

11:18.710 --> 11:21.474
I AGREE WITH PHILIP.

11:21.510 --> 11:23.842
WE DON'T NEED TO END
THE OPERATION.

11:23.880 --> 11:26.815
WE'RE NOT THERE.
MARTHA MAY STILL BE OF USE.

11:26.850 --> 11:29.512
SHE TOLD YOU THE MAIL ROBOT
IS BEING REPAIRED?

11:29.550 --> 11:30.642
MM-HMM.

11:30.690 --> 11:33.056
THE CENTRE WANTS YOU
TO BUG IT.

11:36.190 --> 11:38.556
AND THE CENTRE WILL WANT
MARTHA TO SWITCH OUT THE TAPES

11:38.590 --> 11:41.491
IF WE ACTUALLY DO GET
A BUG INTO THE MAIL ROBOT.

11:41.530 --> 11:43.020
NOT NECESSARILY.

11:43.070 --> 11:44.992
WELL, BUT HOW CAN SHE, GABRIEL,
WHEN SHE'LL BE THE PRIME SUSPECT

11:45.030 --> 11:46.839
FOR PU'I'I'ING THE BUG
IN GAAD'S PEN?

11:46.870 --> 11:49.862
THAT'S NOT MY UNDERSTANDING
OF HOW THE OPERATION WILL WORK.

11:49.910 --> 11:51.901
GABRIEL,
I KNOW HOW THESE THINGS GO.

11:51.940 --> 11:53.828
WHAT'S THE ALTERNATIVE
IF IT'S NOT MARTHA?

11:53.880 --> 11:55.905
DOES THE CENTRE HAVE
SOMEONE ELSE INSIDE THE FBI

11:55.940 --> 11:57.544
WHO COULD SWITCH OUT
THE TAPES?

11:57.580 --> 11:59.912
THERE ARE JANITORS, MAILROOM
CLERKS WHO CAN GAIN ACCESS.

11:59.950 --> 12:02.669
WE DON'T WANT TO RISK
THE MARTHA OPERATION

12:02.720 --> 12:05.689
ANY MORE THAN YOU DO.

12:05.720 --> 12:09.258
YOU SHOULD TRUST
THE ORGANIZATION.

12:19.730 --> 12:21.038
YOU WHAT?!

12:21.070 --> 12:24.267
I DID WHAT I HAD TO DO
TO KEEP WORKING WITH YOU.

12:24.310 --> 12:29.236
IF HE COULD IDENTIFY ME,
THERE WAS NO OTHER WAY.
[ SIGHS ]

12:33.920 --> 12:35.217
AND NO ONE SAW YOU?

12:35.250 --> 12:36.376
NO.
YOU'RE SURE?

12:36.420 --> 12:38.786
YEAH.

12:42.420 --> 12:44.251
YOU ALL RIGHT?

12:44.290 --> 12:45.780
I'M FINE.

12:51.330 --> 12:55.130
IT WAS, UH...

12:55.170 --> 12:56.239
MESSY.

12:56.270 --> 13:00.479
IT DIDN'T GO
EXACTLY AS PLANNED.

13:00.510 --> 13:02.102
IT SELDOM DOES.

13:06.150 --> 13:09.745
TH ESE PEOPLE...

13:09.780 --> 13:14.410
MY PEOPLE,
WHAT WE DO...

13:14.460 --> 13:17.258
WHAT WE'VE DONE TO THE BLACKS
IN MY COUNTRY --

13:17.290 --> 13:19.997
IT'S WRONG.

13:21.830 --> 13:23.969
IT HAS TO STOP.

13:25.830 --> 13:28.435
I WILL DO WHATEVER
IS ASKED OF ME

13:28.470 --> 13:31.439
FOR THE CAUSE...

13:31.470 --> 13:33.131
FOR YOU.

13:36.810 --> 13:39.005
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

13:57.330 --> 13:58.866
[ DOOR OPENS ]

14:01.570 --> 14:02.798
[ SIGHS ]
Stan: LONG MEETING.

14:02.840 --> 14:04.637
LONG DAY.

14:04.670 --> 14:06.900
I'M TIRED,
AND I'M HUNGRY.

14:08.240 --> 14:10.970
OH.
IS THAT THE BEST YOU CAN DO?

14:11.010 --> 14:13.649
WHAT SAY I'LL ORDER
SOMETHING FROM ROOM SERVICE

14:13.680 --> 14:15.511
WHEN I GET YOU
BACK TO THE HOTEL?

14:15.550 --> 14:17.984
I LOVE THAT IDEA.
I WANT A BLT.

14:18.020 --> 14:19.647
IT'S A BACON
AND LETI'UCE --

14:19.690 --> 14:22.853
YEAH, I GOT IT.

15:21.780 --> 15:24.419
[ RATCHET CLICKING ]

15:31.590 --> 15:36.892
IT'S ONLY NATURAL THAT YOU
DEVELOPED FEELINGS FOR MARTHA.

15:36.930 --> 15:38.591
I UNDERSTAND.

15:42.140 --> 15:44.938
THANKS FOR
YOUR PERMISSION.

15:46.980 --> 15:49.437
I DIDN'T MEAN IT
LIKE THAT.

15:51.950 --> 15:54.271
[ TOILET FLUSHES IN DISTANCE ]

16:43.170 --> 16:46.389
[ DRAWER OPENS, RUSTLING ]

17:03.920 --> 17:05.979
WHO ARE YOU?

17:06.020 --> 17:08.682
WE'RE HERE
TO REPAIR A MACHINE.

17:11.530 --> 17:13.828
[ Dial tone ]

17:13.860 --> 17:15.418
THAT'S NOT
A GOOD IDEA.

17:18.200 --> 17:19.497
[ RECEIVER HANGS UP ]

17:19.530 --> 17:22.237
IF YOU SCREAM, I WILL HAVE
TO TAPE YOUR MOUTH SHUT

17:22.270 --> 17:23.669
AND YOUR HANDS
AND YOUR FEET.

17:23.710 --> 17:27.532
I DON'T WANT TO HAVE TO DO THAT.
DO YOU UNDERSTAND?

17:49.800 --> 17:52.598
[ BETTY SIGHS ]

17:53.970 --> 17:55.631
WILL IT TAKE LONG?

17:56.900 --> 17:59.539
WHAT YOU CAME HERE
TO DO.

17:59.570 --> 18:02.038
I DON'T KNOW.

18:02.080 --> 18:06.403
NOT VERY, I HOPE.

18:09.650 --> 18:11.709
[ SCOFFS ]

18:11.750 --> 18:14.082
MAY I?
IT'S JUST BILLS.

18:19.130 --> 18:23.760
I LIKE TO COME HERE LATE
AT NIGHT AND DO THE BOOKKEEPING.

18:25.930 --> 18:27.761
I'M USUALLY ALONE.

18:29.600 --> 18:33.570
MOST PEOPLE DON'T LIKE
TO WORK AT NIGHT.

18:33.610 --> 18:35.601
THEY MISS THE STIR,
THE ACTIVITY.

18:35.640 --> 18:37.301
BUT I LIKE IT.

18:37.350 --> 18:41.673
AND WHEN I'M SITTING HERE
IN THE DARK...

18:44.290 --> 18:49.819
...IS WHEN I FEEL
MOST IN TUNE.

18:52.130 --> 18:55.099
MM-HMM.

18:55.130 --> 18:57.291
IN TUNE?

18:57.330 --> 18:58.991
YES.

18:59.030 --> 19:02.693
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

19:06.640 --> 19:12.476
I FEEL CLOSE TO MY HUSBAND.
I FEEL HIS PRESENCE.

19:14.020 --> 19:17.342
DON'T FEEL HIM TONIGHT.

19:17.390 --> 19:19.312
PROBABLY BECAUSE OF YOU.
[ CHUCKLES ]

19:23.060 --> 19:24.459
THIS IS HIM.

19:24.490 --> 19:28.620
THIS IS GIL IN
THE MOTHER-OF-PEARL FRAME.

19:28.660 --> 19:33.120
THE FRAME WAS A WEDDING PRESENT
FROM HIS SISTER, LOUISE.

19:33.170 --> 19:34.535
SHE NEVER MARRIED.

19:34.570 --> 19:38.006
HER PARENTS SAID
IT WAS BECAUSE

19:38.040 --> 19:40.304
SHE WAS TOO GOOD FOR ANY MAN
SHE EVER MET,

19:40.340 --> 19:42.137
BUT SHE WAS A PILL.

19:42.180 --> 19:43.841
HMM.

19:47.180 --> 19:49.239
THIS IS ME.

19:52.190 --> 19:54.658
YOU'RE VERY PRETTY.

19:54.690 --> 19:57.158
YES, I WAS.

19:57.190 --> 19:58.828
AND THIS IS...?

19:58.860 --> 20:01.055
ANDY. [ CHUCKLES ]

20:01.100 --> 20:03.523
HE RUNS THINGS NOW.

20:07.270 --> 20:09.693
H-HE WON'T BE HERE
TILL MORNING.

20:19.610 --> 20:24.013
GIL STARTED THE SHOP.
HE WAS A MACHINIST.

20:24.050 --> 20:29.852
HE LEARNED THE MACHINIST TRADE
IN THE ARMY, WORLD WAR II.

20:29.890 --> 20:33.849
I TAUGHT MATH,
LITTLE CHILDREN.

20:33.900 --> 20:36.255
I-I WAS GOOD
WITH NUMBERS.

20:36.300 --> 20:41.090
IT WASN'T, UH,
CALCULATORS AND ROBOTS THEN.

20:41.140 --> 20:44.303
[ CHUCKLES ]
WELL, THE WORLD CHANGES.

20:46.940 --> 20:49.238
SOME THINGS
STAY THE SAME.

20:52.580 --> 20:55.572
THAT ONE
WAS TAKEN IN FRANCE.

20:55.620 --> 20:59.215
HE WAS FOUR YEARS
IN EUROPE.

20:59.250 --> 21:01.559
GIL'S REGIMENT
FREED JEWISH PEOPLE

21:01.590 --> 21:03.956
FROM
THE CONCENTRATION CAM PS.

21:03.990 --> 21:05.389
[ SIGHS ]

21:05.430 --> 21:09.218
H-HE WASN'T JEWISH.
HE WAS CHRISTIAN SCIENTIST.

21:09.260 --> 21:12.388
BUT AFTER THE WAR...

21:12.430 --> 21:14.295
HE WASN'T ANYTHING.

21:14.340 --> 21:17.730
I WOULD TAKE ANDY
TO CHURCH,

21:17.770 --> 21:23.606
BUT GIL SAID HE HAD NO USE
FOR THOSE STORIES.

21:26.680 --> 21:30.616
WHAT HE S-- WHAT HE SAW,
IT STAYED WITH HIM.

21:33.620 --> 21:35.508
[ SIGHS ]

21:39.460 --> 21:41.496
MAY I HAVE
A GLASS OF WATER?

21:50.840 --> 21:52.467
I JUST NEED YOUR KEYS.

21:52.510 --> 21:54.831
OH.

21:54.880 --> 21:56.336
[ DRAWER OPENS ]

21:57.380 --> 21:59.302
[ DRAWER CLOSES ]

22:22.840 --> 22:26.003
[ RATCHET CLICKING ]

22:36.520 --> 22:38.147
IT'S AN OLD WOMAN.

22:38.190 --> 22:39.646
HER HUSBAND
STARTED THE BUSINESS.

22:39.690 --> 22:41.351
SHE COMES IN AT NIGHT
TO PAY BILLS.

22:41.390 --> 22:43.187
AT NIGHT?

22:43.220 --> 22:45.529
SHE LIKES IT
WHEN IT'S QUIET.

22:50.360 --> 22:51.566
HOW MUCH LONGER
DO YOU HAVE?

22:51.600 --> 22:54.489
I'M TRYING, ELIZABETH.

22:54.540 --> 22:57.031
NO, I KNOW. I'M...

23:02.040 --> 23:05.339
[ SIGHS ]

23:05.380 --> 23:07.746
HE WAS GONE FOR FOUR YEARS
DURING WORLD WAR II,

23:07.780 --> 23:09.042
HER HUSBAND.

23:16.220 --> 23:18.381
SHE PICKED A BAD TIME.

23:32.240 --> 23:34.606
ONE SEC.

23:46.590 --> 23:49.889
OKAY, I'LL WAIT OUTSIDE
TILL THE FOOD COMES.

23:49.920 --> 23:51.729
FRONT DESK
SAID IT WON'T BE LONG.

23:51.760 --> 23:53.728
YOU'RE VERY GOOD TO ME,
STAN.

23:53.760 --> 23:56.399
I'LL BRING IT TO YOU
AS SOON AS IT GETS HERE.

23:56.430 --> 23:57.920
THANK YOU.

24:01.440 --> 24:04.762
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

24:04.810 --> 24:07.472
[ SIGHS ]

24:24.460 --> 24:27.088
[ PILLS RATTLING ]

24:27.130 --> 24:29.758
I HAVE A BAD HEART.

24:29.800 --> 24:33.429
THEY SAY
THAT I NEED A NEW ONE,

24:33.470 --> 24:36.268
BUT I DON'T WANT
A NEW HEART.

24:36.300 --> 24:37.961
UH-HUH.

24:41.810 --> 24:44.176
[ SIGHS ] WHAT --
WHAT WOULD I DO WITH IT?

24:45.880 --> 24:48.269
[ SIGHS ]

24:48.320 --> 24:49.810
WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

24:51.990 --> 24:53.184
ELIZABETH.

24:53.220 --> 24:55.984
ARE YOU A ROBBER?

24:58.160 --> 24:59.457
NO.

24:59.490 --> 25:01.958
NO, RIGHT.

25:02.000 --> 25:03.297
RIGHT.

25:03.330 --> 25:07.699
YOU CAME HERE
TO FIX SOMETHING.

25:07.740 --> 25:08.798
RIGHT.

25:08.840 --> 25:10.159
AH.

25:10.200 --> 25:13.829
"ALL -- ALL MARBLES PRESENT
AND ACCOUNTED FOR."

25:13.880 --> 25:17.304
THAT'S SOMETHING THAT MY FATHER
USED TO SAY EVERY MORNING

25:17.340 --> 25:19.149
BEFORE HE STARTED WORK.

25:19.180 --> 25:21.375
WHAT DID HE DO?

25:21.420 --> 25:23.513
HE WAS A FARMER.

25:24.520 --> 25:27.318
ANDY SAID
THE FARM IS A VINEYARD NOW.

25:27.350 --> 25:29.489
A VINEYARD,
LIKE IN FRANCE.

25:29.520 --> 25:31.886
YEAH. YOURS?

25:34.200 --> 25:36.998
HE WAS A COAL MINER.

25:37.030 --> 25:39.328
YOUR MOTHER?

25:39.370 --> 25:42.168
AN OFFICE WORKER.

25:42.200 --> 25:47.502
AND SHE COOKED, CLEANED,
WAITED IN LINE FOR FOOD.

25:47.540 --> 25:49.508
OH, DEAR.

25:49.540 --> 25:51.576
IS SHE ALIVE?

25:53.450 --> 25:55.372
YES.

25:55.420 --> 25:57.581
WHERE DOES SHE LIVE?

26:02.060 --> 26:04.051
RUSSIA.

26:10.400 --> 26:12.425
YOUR ENGLISH
IS VERY GOOD.

26:12.470 --> 26:16.065
I'VE BEEN WELL-TRAINED.

26:20.470 --> 26:23.530
[Voice breaking ]
YEAH.

26:23.580 --> 26:25.969
YOU AREN'T GOING
TO LET ME LEAVE...

26:30.580 --> 26:32.081
...ARE YOU?

26:34.160 --> 26:36.913
IT'S NOT POSSIBLE,
NO.

26:42.130 --> 26:43.597
OHH.

26:45.800 --> 26:49.566
OOH, THIS IS NOT
HOW I EXPECTED IT TO END.

26:49.600 --> 26:51.409
[ CHUCKLES ]

26:51.440 --> 26:53.772
THE -- THE STORY.

27:00.850 --> 27:02.977
I'M NOT AFRAID
OF LEAVING THE WORLD.

27:03.020 --> 27:05.238
I-I DON'T KNOW WHY,
BUT I'M -- I'M NOT.

27:05.290 --> 27:10.751
IT'S BETTER THAN FALLING DOWN
IN THE STREET LIKE A DRUNK

27:10.790 --> 27:13.452
AND WAITING FOR
SOME STRANGER TO PASS BY.

27:13.490 --> 27:18.860
OR SITTING IN FRONT OF
THE TELEVISION ALONE.

27:21.140 --> 27:23.597
OH, I HATE HOSPITALS.

27:23.640 --> 27:28.976
WHEN GIL WAS SICK,
I HATED TO GO SEE HIM THERE.

27:29.010 --> 27:32.002
I WENT, BUT I HATED IT,
EVERYTHING ABOUT IT.

28:36.240 --> 28:38.242
AH.

28:51.730 --> 28:54.528
[ SIGHS ]

28:54.560 --> 28:56.050
[THUD]

28:58.270 --> 29:00.124
HELLO?

29:05.270 --> 29:06.532
STAN?

29:06.570 --> 29:07.901
[ SPEAKS RUSSIAN ]

30:36.500 --> 30:38.297
[ SHOUTS ]

30:38.330 --> 30:39.490
[ GRUNTS ]

30:40.500 --> 30:43.162
[ GRUNTS ]

30:44.510 --> 30:46.205
STAN !

30:46.240 --> 30:47.969
OHH.

30:48.010 --> 30:49.307
UGH.

30:49.340 --> 30:51.479
OH, YOU'RE HURT.

30:51.510 --> 30:53.307
I GOT IT. I GOT IT.

30:53.350 --> 30:55.477
[ GROANS ]

30:55.520 --> 30:58.318
[ SPEAKS RUSSIAN ]

30:58.350 --> 31:01.012
[ GROANS ]

31:09.200 --> 31:11.521
[ VIDEO GAME BEEPING ]

31:13.100 --> 31:14.897
IT'S LATE, HENRY.
GIVE IT A REST.

31:14.940 --> 31:16.362
I'M ALMOST DONE.

31:16.400 --> 31:19.198
YOU KNOW HOW YOU GET
WHEN YOU DON'T GET ENOUGH SLEEP.

31:19.240 --> 31:21.435
I'M ALMOST DONE.

31:23.780 --> 31:25.543
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

31:59.750 --> 32:01.945
[ CLATTER ]

32:01.980 --> 32:06.747
A-ARE YOU MARRIED?

32:06.790 --> 32:08.553
YES.

32:08.590 --> 32:12.048
THAT'S GOOD, TO HAVE
A-A PARTNER, A-A F-FRIEND.

32:12.090 --> 32:15.059
GIL AND I
WERE MARRIED TWICE.

32:15.100 --> 32:16.727
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

32:16.760 --> 32:20.218
WE GOT DIVORCED.

32:20.270 --> 32:24.229
HE REMARRIED, BUT HIS WIFE DIED
IN AN ACCIDENT,

32:24.270 --> 32:28.730
AND WE DID IT AGAIN.
[ CHUCKLES ]

32:28.780 --> 32:30.736
[ GROANS ]

32:30.780 --> 32:32.145
OH.

32:37.280 --> 32:38.747
[ GASPS ]

32:38.790 --> 32:41.987
WE NO LONGER HAD
SUGAR IN OUR EYES.

32:42.020 --> 32:43.658
[ CHUCKLES ]

32:43.690 --> 32:46.750
N-NONE OF THAT, UH,

32:46.790 --> 32:48.929
"WHY CAN'T YOU BE
THE PERSON I WANT

32:48.960 --> 32:51.269
INSTEAD OF
THE PERSON YOU ARE?" STUFF.

32:51.300 --> 32:54.963
THIS TIME,
IT STUCK LIKE GLUE.

32:55.000 --> 32:58.766
WE WERE 27 YEARS.

32:58.810 --> 33:02.632
WE WERE HAPPY IN THE SEC--
SECOND ROUND.

33:02.680 --> 33:05.001
THERE ARE ONLY
TWO THINGS

33:05.050 --> 33:10.647
THAT GIL WOULD NEVER SAY
A BLESSED WORD ABOUT.

33:10.680 --> 33:12.682
HELEN.

33:12.720 --> 33:14.859
[ CHUCKLES ]

33:14.890 --> 33:18.018
THE OTHER WOMAN.
MY NEMESIS.

33:18.060 --> 33:19.687
NO, MY BEST FRIEND.

33:22.860 --> 33:24.327
WHAT WAS
THE OTHER THING?

33:24.370 --> 33:31.708
THE -- THE WAR,
OF C-- OF COURSE.

33:38.510 --> 33:41.172
DID GIL SEND YOU?

33:45.520 --> 33:46.987
YES.

33:47.020 --> 33:51.525
DID HE TELL YOU
I'M AFRAID OF PAIN?

33:53.390 --> 33:54.698
MM-HMM.

33:59.030 --> 34:00.827
IS HE WITH HELEN?

34:00.870 --> 34:04.203
NO. NO.

34:04.240 --> 34:06.037
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

34:09.040 --> 34:12.168
I DON'T WANT
ANYTHING TO HAPPEN TO ANDY.

34:12.210 --> 34:16.670
HE'S A GOOD --
HE'S A GOOD SON.

34:16.720 --> 34:18.017
NOTHING'S GONNA HAPPEN
TO HIM.

34:18.050 --> 34:20.018
PROMISE?

34:20.050 --> 34:22.712
I PROMISE.

34:27.060 --> 34:28.425
DO YOU HAVE CHILDREN?

34:28.460 --> 34:30.849
YES.

34:30.900 --> 34:35.394
AND THIS IS
WHAT YOU DO?

34:37.900 --> 34:39.060
SOMETIMES.

34:39.110 --> 34:41.874
BY YOURSELF?

34:41.910 --> 34:45.243
WITH MY HUSBAND.

34:46.910 --> 34:49.572
WHY?

34:51.420 --> 34:55.049
TO MAKE THE WORLD
A BETTER PLACE.

34:55.090 --> 34:58.878
YOU THINK
DOING THIS TO ME

34:58.930 --> 35:02.252
WILL MAKE THE WORLD
A BETTER PLACE?

35:03.960 --> 35:06.599
I'M SORRY,
BUT IT WILL.

35:08.440 --> 35:11.807
THAT'S WHAT EVIL PEOPLE
TELL THEMSELVES

35:11.840 --> 35:15.776
WHEN THEY DO
EVIL THINGS.

35:19.950 --> 35:21.577
OH.

35:21.620 --> 35:24.441
[ SHIVERING ]

35:28.620 --> 35:32.750
[ Breathing heavily ]
I...CAN'T...CAN'T...

35:32.790 --> 35:33.825
CAN'T...

35:33.860 --> 35:35.828
[ BREATHING RAPIDLY]

35:35.860 --> 35:37.452
CAN'T...CAN'T. ..

35:44.640 --> 35:46.801
[ WHEEZING ]

36:07.830 --> 36:12.119
1-2-3.

36:12.170 --> 36:13.819
Philip: 1-2-3.

36:18.510 --> 36:20.159
WHAT HAPPENED?

36:20.210 --> 36:23.532
THEY'LL FIND HER BODY
IN THE MORNING. SHE WAS SICK.

36:26.580 --> 36:28.172
YOU OKAY?

36:30.020 --> 36:32.181
ELIZABETH?

36:33.420 --> 36:35.183
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
[ SNIFFLES ]

36:37.020 --> 36:38.385
WE HAVE TO GO.

36:55.280 --> 36:56.338
Aderholt: HOW LONG
WAS SHE ALONE IN THE ROOM?

36:56.380 --> 36:58.701
NO MORE THAN 10 MINUTES.

36:58.750 --> 37:00.069
GUY MUST HAVE COME IN
THROUGH A WINDOW.

37:00.110 --> 37:02.510
MAYBE
HE WAS ALREADY THERE.

37:02.550 --> 37:03.847
HIDING?

37:03.880 --> 37:06.041
IN A CLOSET,
UNDER A BED.

37:06.090 --> 37:08.012
YOU CHECKED THE ROOM
FIRST?

37:08.050 --> 37:10.257
YEAH.

37:10.290 --> 37:12.588
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

37:12.630 --> 37:17.351
I GOT A HELL OF A HEADACHE,
BUT OTHER THAN THAT, I'M GOOD.

37:17.400 --> 37:19.527
TAKE SOME ASPIRIN?

37:19.570 --> 37:21.265
YEAH.

37:21.300 --> 37:23.188
IT WORKS BETTER
IF YOU TAKE IT WITH BEER.

37:23.240 --> 37:25.367
IT'S NOT SUPPOSED TO,
BUT IT DOES.

37:25.410 --> 37:27.059
GO HOME. GET SOME REST.

37:27.110 --> 37:31.547
DON'T WORRY.
WE'LL BEEF UP HER SECURITY.

37:31.580 --> 37:34.413
OKAY. THAN KS.

37:36.480 --> 37:39.415
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

37:53.100 --> 37:56.069
[ SNIFFLES ]

37:56.100 --> 37:57.237
[ COUGHS ]

37:57.270 --> 38:00.398
WELL...
[ SNIFFLES ]

38:00.440 --> 38:03.238
SHE DIDN'T
BREAK OR CONFESS

38:03.280 --> 38:05.601
OR PANIC.

38:08.180 --> 38:11.411
MAYBE SHE WAS IN SHOCK,

38:11.450 --> 38:14.283
THINKING
SHE WAS GONNA DIE.

38:15.620 --> 38:18.157
HAS ANYBODY SAID ANYTHING
AT THE REZIDENTURA?

38:18.190 --> 38:21.956
NO. NOTHING YET.

38:22.000 --> 38:23.627
[ PILLS RATTLE ]

38:28.640 --> 38:30.494
[ TAB POPS ]

38:34.310 --> 38:36.972
NOT FOR ME.

38:39.180 --> 38:41.273
HOW'S YOUR HEAD?

38:41.310 --> 38:43.949
IT'S FELT BETTER.

38:43.980 --> 38:48.314
SORRY TO HIT YOU
SO HARD.

38:48.360 --> 38:50.783
TRY IT WITH A RAW EGG.

38:50.820 --> 38:53.459
IT'S WHAT WE DO...
FOR A HANGOVER.

38:53.490 --> 38:55.822
I DON'T HAVE
A HANGOVER.

39:00.900 --> 39:03.835
I THINK
I'LL HAVE ONE.

39:10.180 --> 39:12.045
WASN'T THERE JUST
A LITTLE PART OF YOU

39:12.080 --> 39:13.843
THAT WANTED
TO CRACK MY HEAD OPEN?

39:18.420 --> 39:19.910
[ TAB POPS ]

39:22.520 --> 39:26.183
"GEODE."
THAT'S VERY NICE.

39:26.230 --> 39:28.494
DON'T -- DON'T DO THAT.

39:28.530 --> 39:31.522
WELL, IT'S JUST A STRONG WORD.
THAT'S ALL I'M SAYING.

39:32.870 --> 39:34.599
17.

39:35.200 --> 39:37.498
[ SIGHS ]

39:37.540 --> 39:42.375
STUCK BETWEEN A GEODE
AND A HARD PLACE.

39:50.220 --> 39:53.018
"AMATORY"?

39:53.050 --> 39:54.347
24.

39:54.390 --> 39:56.017
YES, 24.

39:56.060 --> 40:00.019
LOVING,
DEVOTED, ADORING.

40:00.060 --> 40:02.221
[ SIGHS ]

40:02.260 --> 40:03.693
WHERE DO YOU COME UP WITH
THIS STUFF?

40:03.730 --> 40:06.858
I LOVE WORDS.
THEY LEAVE A TRAIL.

40:06.900 --> 40:11.735
FOR EXAMPLE, "AMATORY"
IS FROM THE LATIN WORD FOR LOVE,

40:11.770 --> 40:17.072
WHILE "WEDLOCK" -- THE CONDITION
OF BEING MARRIED --

40:17.110 --> 40:19.408
IS NORSE, NORWEGIAN.

40:19.450 --> 40:22.374
WED...LOCK. HMM?

40:22.420 --> 40:24.047
WHICH MEANS
"PERPETUAL BATTLE."

40:24.080 --> 40:25.388
YOUR POINT BEING?

40:25.420 --> 40:28.548
LOVE AND MARRIAGE
IN MANY WAYS ARE ANTITHETICAL.

40:28.590 --> 40:32.378
ONE IS A BOLT OF LIGHTNING,
AN EPIPHANY.

40:32.430 --> 40:36.753
AND THE OTHER IS
PLANTING, TILLING, TENDING.

40:36.800 --> 40:40.292
IT'S HARD WORK.
I'M -- I'M TRYING
TO CONCENTRATE HERE.

40:40.330 --> 40:42.594
OH, I'M SORRY.

40:47.440 --> 40:52.070
OH, OKAY.

40:52.110 --> 40:54.647
"SPHINX."

40:54.680 --> 40:56.443
EXCELLENT.

40:57.480 --> 41:00.244
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

41:00.290 --> 41:02.781
59. BRAVO.

41:07.790 --> 41:10.452
WHEN I FIRST SAW
ELIZABETH...

41:12.300 --> 41:14.268
...IT --
IT FELT LIKE A --

41:14.300 --> 41:16.029
A BOLT OF LIGHTNING?

41:19.970 --> 41:22.768
IT HAD NEVER HAPPENED
BEFORE.

41:22.810 --> 41:23.777
OR SINCE.

41:23.810 --> 41:26.802
MAY I SHARE SOMETHING
WITH YOU?

41:26.850 --> 41:28.943
MM-HMM.

41:28.980 --> 41:31.949
ELIZABETH REJECT ED
THE FIRST OFFICER

41:31.990 --> 41:34.288
PROPOSED TO BE HER HUSBAND
IN AMERICA.

41:34.320 --> 41:38.484
WELL, IN HER OWN WAY,
SHE CHOSE YOU.

41:42.500 --> 41:46.163
IT NEVER FELT LIKE THAT
TO -- TO ME.

41:46.200 --> 41:48.896
NEVERTHELESS,
IT'S TRUE.

41:57.910 --> 42:00.504
PHILIP, WOULD YOU LIKE
TO TELL ME WHAT'S GOING ON?

42:00.550 --> 42:03.018
YOU'RE NOT IN THIS ALONE,
YOU KNOW.

42:03.050 --> 42:07.009
ELIZABETH LOVES YOU. I LOVE YOU.
WHAT'S THE PROBLEM?

42:10.190 --> 42:12.727
THE -- THE PROBLEM?

42:13.860 --> 42:19.059
THE PROBLEM IS YOU,
GABRIEL.

42:19.100 --> 42:22.160
AND ALL THIS TALK.

42:22.200 --> 42:25.909
ALL THIS TALK.

42:25.940 --> 42:29.376
BECAUSE YOU THINK YOU CAN WRAP
ME AROUND YOUR LITTLE FINGER.

42:29.410 --> 42:31.503
BUT I'M NOT ELIZABETH.

42:31.540 --> 42:32.507
I'M AWARE OF THAT.

42:32.550 --> 42:35.178
I TRUSTED YOU.

42:35.220 --> 42:37.040
I TRUSTED YOU.

42:37.080 --> 42:40.880
AND YOUR JOB WAS TO LOOK OUT
FOR ME. IT WAS.

42:43.220 --> 42:47.259
AND NOW MY JOB IS TO LOOK OUT
FOR MY FAMILY,

42:47.290 --> 42:50.020
BECAUSE
NO ONE ELSE WILL.
